 499    @classmethod
 500    async def a_get(
 501        cls,
 502        session: Session,
 503        account_number: Optional[str] = None,
 504        include_closed: bool = False,
 505    ) -> Union[Self, list[Self]]:
 506        """
 507        Gets all trading accounts associated with the Tastytrade user, or a specific
 508        one if given an account ID.
 509
 510        :param session: the session to use for the request.
 511        :param account_number: the account ID to get.
 512        :param include_closed: whether to include closed accounts in the results
 513        """
 514        if account_number:
 515            data = await session._a_get(f"/customers/me/accounts/{account_number}")
 516            return cls(**data)
 517        data = await session._a_get("/customers/me/accounts")
 518        return [
 519            cls(**i["account"])
 520            for i in data["items"]
 521            if include_closed or not i["account"]["is-closed"]
 522        ]

 553        return [

 555            for i in data["items"]

 595    async def a_get_balance_snapshots(
 596        self,
 597        session: Session,
 598        per_page: int = 250,
 599        page_offset: Optional[int] = None,
 600        currency: str = "USD",
 601        end_date: Optional[date] = None,
 602        start_date: Optional[date] = None,
 603        snapshot_date: Optional[date] = None,
 604        time_of_day: Literal["BOD", "EOD"] = "EOD",
 605    ) -> list[AccountBalanceSnapshot]:
 606        """
 607        Returns a list of balance snapshots. This list will
 608        just have a few snapshots if you don't pass a start
 609        date; otherwise, it will be each day's balances in
 610        the given range.
 611
 612        :param session: the session to use for the request.
 613        :param currency: the currency to show balances in.
 614        :param start_date: the starting date of the range.
 615        :param end_date: the ending date of the range.
 616        :param snapshot_date: the date of the snapshot to get.
 617        :param time_of_day:
 618            the time of day of the snapshots to get, either 'EOD' (End Of Day) or 'BOD' (Beginning Of Day).
 619        """
 620        paginate = False
 621        if page_offset is None:
 622            page_offset = 0
 623            paginate = True
 624        params = {
 625            "per-page": per_page,
 626            "page-offset": page_offset,
 627            "currency": currency,
 628            "end-date": end_date,
 629            "start-date": start_date,
 630            "snapshot-date": snapshot_date,
 631            "time-of-day": time_of_day,
 632        }
 633        snapshots = []
 634        while True:
 635            response = await session.async_client.get(
 636                f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/balance-snapshots",
 637                params={
 638                    k: v  # type: ignore
 639                    for k, v in params.items()
 640                    if v is not None
 641                },
 642            )
 643            validate_response(response)
 644            json = response.json()
 645            snapshots.extend(
 646                [AccountBalanceSnapshot(**i) for i in json["data"]["items"]]
 647            )
 648            # handle pagination
 649            pagination = json["pagination"]
 650            if (
 651                pagination["page-offset"] >= pagination["total-pages"] - 1
 652                or not paginate
 653            ):
 654                break
 655            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore
 656        return snapshots

 721    async def a_get_positions(
 722        self,
 723        session: Session,
 724        underlying_symbols: Optional[list[str]] = None,
 725        symbol: Optional[str] = None,
 726        instrument_type: Optional[InstrumentType] = None,
 727        include_closed: Optional[bool] = None,
 728        underlying_product_code: Optional[str] = None,
 729        partition_keys: Optional[list[str]] = None,
 730        net_positions: Optional[bool] = None,
 731        include_marks: Optional[bool] = None,
 732    ) -> list[CurrentPosition]:
 733        """
 734        Get the current positions of the account.
 735
 736        :param session: the session to use for the request.
 737        :param underlying_symbols:
 738            an array of underlying symbols for positions.
 739        :param symbol: a single symbol.
 740        :param instrument_type: the type of instrument.
 741        :param include_closed:
 742            if closed positions should be included in the query.
 743        :param underlying_product_code: the underlying future's product code.
 744        :param partition_keys: account partition keys.
 745        :param net_positions:
 746            returns net positions grouped by instrument type and symbol.
 747        :param include_marks:
 748            include current quote mark (note: can decrease performance).
 749        """
 750        params = {
 751            "underlying-symbol[]": underlying_symbols,
 752            "symbol": symbol,
 753            "instrument-type": instrument_type.value if instrument_type else None,
 754            "include-closed-positions": include_closed,
 755            "underlying-product-code": underlying_product_code,
 756            "partition-keys[]": partition_keys,
 757            "net-positions": net_positions,
 758            "include-marks": include_marks,
 759        }
 760        data = await session._a_get(
 761            f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/positions",
 762            params={k: v for k, v in params.items() if v is not None},
 763        )
 764        return [CurrentPosition(**i) for i in data["items"]]

 811    async def a_get_history(
 812        self,
 813        session: Session,
 814        per_page: int = 250,
 815        page_offset: Optional[int] = None,
 816        sort: str = "Desc",
 817        type: Optional[str] = None,
 818        types: Optional[list[str]] = None,
 819        sub_types: Optional[list[str]] = None,
 820        start_date: Optional[date] = None,
 821        end_date: Optional[date] = None,
 822        instrument_type: Optional[InstrumentType] = None,
 823        symbol: Optional[str] = None,
 824        underlying_symbol: Optional[str] = None,
 825        action: Optional[str] = None,
 826        partition_key: Optional[str] = None,
 827        futures_symbol: Optional[str] = None,
 828        start_at: Optional[datetime] = None,
 829        end_at: Optional[datetime] = None,
 830    ) -> list[Transaction]:
 831        """
 832        Get transaction history of the account.
 833
 834        :param session: the session to use for the request.
 835        :param per_page: the number of results to return per page.
 836        :param page_offset:
 837            provide a specific page to get; if not provided, get all pages
 838        :param sort: the order to sort results in, either 'Desc' or 'Asc'.
 839        :param type: the type of transaction.
 840        :param types: a list of transaction types to filter by.
 841        :param sub_types: an array of transaction subtypes to filter by.
 842        :param start_date: the start date of transactions to query.
 843        :param end_date: the end date of transactions to query.
 844        :param instrument_type: the type of instrument.
 845        :param symbol: a single symbol.
 846        :param underlying_symbol: the underlying symbol.
 847        :param action:
 848            the action of the transaction: 'Sell to Open', 'Sell to Close',
 849            'Buy to Open', 'Buy to Close', 'Sell' or 'Buy'.
 850        :param partition_key: account partition key.
 851        :param futures_symbol: the full TW Future Symbol, e.g. /ESZ9, /NGZ19.
 852        :param start_at:
 853            datetime start range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
 854        :param end_at:
 855            datetime end range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
 856        """
 857        # if a specific page is provided, we just get that page;
 858        # otherwise, we loop through all pages
 859        paginate = False
 860        if page_offset is None:
 861            page_offset = 0
 862            paginate = True
 863        params = {
 864            "per-page": per_page,
 865            "page-offset": page_offset,
 866            "sort": sort,
 867            "type": type,
 868            "types[]": types,
 869            "sub-type[]": sub_types,
 870            "start-date": start_date,
 871            "end-date": end_date,
 872            "instrument-type": instrument_type.value if instrument_type else None,
 873            "symbol": symbol,
 874            "underlying-symbol": underlying_symbol,
 875            "action": action,
 876            "partition-key": partition_key,
 877            "futures-symbol": futures_symbol,
 878            "start-at": start_at,
 879            "end-at": end_at,
 880        }
 881        # loop through pages and get all transactions
 882        txns = []
 883        while True:
 884            response = await session.async_client.get(
 885                f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/transactions",
 886                params={
 887                    k: v  # type: ignore
 888                    for k, v in params.items()
 889                    if v is not None
 890                },
 891            )
 892            validate_response(response)
 893            json = response.json()
 894            txns.extend([Transaction(**i) for i in json["data"]["items"]])
 895            # handle pagination
 896            pagination = json["pagination"]
 897            if (
 898                pagination["page-offset"] >= pagination["total-pages"] - 1
 899                or not paginate
 900            ):
 901                break
 902            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore
 903
 904        return txns

 994                or not paginate
 995            ):
 996                break
 997            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore

1055    async def a_get_net_liquidating_value_history(
1056        self,
1057        session: Session,
1058        time_back: Optional[str] = None,
1059        start_time: Optional[datetime] = None,
1060    ) -> list[NetLiqOhlc]:
1061        """
1062        Returns a list of account net liquidating value snapshots over the
1063        specified time period.
1064
1065        :param session:
1066            the session to use for the request, can't be certification.
1067        :param time_back:
1068            the time period to get net liquidating value snapshots for. This
1069            param is required if start_time is not given. Possible values are:
1070            '1d', '1m', '3m', '6m', '1y', 'all'.
1071        :param start_time:
1072            the start point for the query. This param is required is time-back
1073            is not given. If given, will take precedence over time-back.
1074        """
1075        params = {}
1076        if start_time:
1077            # format to Tastytrade DateTime format
1078            params = {"start-time": start_time.strftime(TT_DATE_FMT)}
1079        elif not time_back:
1080            msg = "Either time_back or start_time must be specified."
1081            raise TastytradeError(msg)
1082        else:
1083            params = {"time-back": time_back}
1084        data = await session._a_get(
1085            f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/net-liq/history", params=params
1086        )
1087        return [NetLiqOhlc(**i) for i in data["items"]]

1323    async def a_get_order_history(
1324        self,
1325        session: Session,
1326        per_page: int = 50,
1327        page_offset: Optional[int] = None,
1328        start_date: Optional[date] = None,
1329        end_date: Optional[date] = None,
1330        underlying_symbol: Optional[str] = None,
1331        statuses: Optional[list[OrderStatus]] = None,
1332        futures_symbol: Optional[str] = None,
1333        underlying_instrument_type: Optional[InstrumentType] = None,
1334        sort: Optional[str] = None,
1335        start_at: Optional[datetime] = None,
1336        end_at: Optional[datetime] = None,
1337    ) -> list[PlacedOrder]:
1338        """
1339        Get order history of the account.
1340
1341        :param session: the session to use for the request.
1342        :param per_page: the number of results to return per page.
1343        :param page_offset:
1344            provide a specific page to get; if not provided, get all pages
1345        :param start_date: the start date of orders to query.
1346        :param end_date: the end date of orders to query.
1347        :param underlying_symbol: underlying symbol to filter by.
1348        :param statuses: a list of statuses to filter by.
1349        :param futures_symbol:
1350            Tastytrade future symbol for futures and future options.
1351        :param underlying_instrument_type: the type of instrument to filter by
1352        :param sort: the order to sort results in, either 'Desc' or 'Asc'.
1353        :param start_at:
1354            datetime start range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
1355        :param end_at:
1356            datetime end range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
1357        """
1358        # if a specific page is provided, we just get that page;
1359        # otherwise, we loop through all pages
1360        paginate = False
1361        if page_offset is None:
1362            page_offset = 0
1363            paginate = True
1364        params = {
1365            "per-page": per_page,
1366            "page-offset": page_offset,
1367            "start-date": start_date,
1368            "end-date": end_date,
1369            "underlying-symbol": underlying_symbol,
1370            "status[]": [s.value for s in statuses] if statuses else None,
1371            "futures-symbol": futures_symbol,
1372            "underlying-instrument-type": underlying_instrument_type.value
1373            if underlying_instrument_type
1374            else None,
1375            "sort": sort,
1376            "start-at": start_at,
1377            "end-at": end_at,
1378        }
1379        # loop through pages and get all transactions
1380        orders = []
1381        while True:
1382            response = await session.async_client.get(
1383                f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/orders",
1384                params={
1385                    k: v  # type: ignore
1386                    for k, v in params.items()
1387                    if v is not None
1388                },
1389            )
1390            validate_response(response)
1391            json = response.json()
1392            orders.extend([PlacedOrder(**i) for i in json["data"]["items"]])
1393            # handle pagination
1394            pagination = json["pagination"]
1395            if (
1396                pagination["page-offset"] >= pagination["total-pages"] - 1
1397                or not paginate
1398            ):
1399                break
1400            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore
1401
1402        return orders

595    async def a_get_balance_snapshots(
596        self,
597        session: Session,
598        per_page: int = 250,
599        page_offset: Optional[int] = None,
600        currency: str = "USD",
601        end_date: Optional[date] = None,
602        start_date: Optional[date] = None,
603        snapshot_date: Optional[date] = None,
604        time_of_day: Literal["BOD", "EOD"] = "EOD",
605    ) -> list[AccountBalanceSnapshot]:
606        """
607        Returns a list of balance snapshots. This list will
608        just have a few snapshots if you don't pass a start
609        date; otherwise, it will be each day's balances in
610        the given range.
611
612        :param session: the session to use for the request.
613        :param currency: the currency to show balances in.
614        :param start_date: the starting date of the range.
615        :param end_date: the ending date of the range.
616        :param snapshot_date: the date of the snapshot to get.
617        :param time_of_day:
618            the time of day of the snapshots to get, either 'EOD' (End Of Day) or 'BOD' (Beginning Of Day).
619        """
620        paginate = False
621        if page_offset is None:
622            page_offset = 0
623            paginate = True
624        params = {
625            "per-page": per_page,
626            "page-offset": page_offset,
627            "currency": currency,
628            "end-date": end_date,
629            "start-date": start_date,
630            "snapshot-date": snapshot_date,
631            "time-of-day": time_of_day,
632        }
633        snapshots = []
634        while True:
635            response = await session.async_client.get(
636                f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/balance-snapshots",
637                params={
638                    k: v  # type: ignore
639                    for k, v in params.items()
640                    if v is not None
641                },
642            )
643            validate_response(response)
644            json = response.json()
645            snapshots.extend(
646                [AccountBalanceSnapshot(**i) for i in json["data"]["items"]]
647            )
648            # handle pagination
649            pagination = json["pagination"]
650            if (
651                pagination["page-offset"] >= pagination["total-pages"] - 1
652                or not paginate
653            ):
654                break
655            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore
656        return snapshots

816        sort: str = "Desc",

820        start_date: Optional[date] = None,

823        symbol: Optional[str] = None,

830    ) -> list[Transaction]:
831        """
832        Get transaction history of the account.
833
834        :param session: the session to use for the request.
835        :param per_page: the number of results to return per page.
836        :param page_offset:
837            provide a specific page to get; if not provided, get all pages
838        :param sort: the order to sort results in, either 'Desc' or 'Asc'.
839        :param type: the type of transaction.
840        :param types: a list of transaction types to filter by.
841        :param sub_types: an array of transaction subtypes to filter by.
842        :param start_date: the start date of transactions to query.
843        :param end_date: the end date of transactions to query.
844        :param instrument_type: the type of instrument.
845        :param symbol: a single symbol.
846        :param underlying_symbol: the underlying symbol.
847        :param action:
848            the action of the transaction: 'Sell to Open', 'Sell to Close',
849            'Buy to Open', 'Buy to Close', 'Sell' or 'Buy'.
850        :param partition_key: account partition key.
851        :param futures_symbol: the full TW Future Symbol, e.g. /ESZ9, /NGZ19.
852        :param start_at:
853            datetime start range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
854        :param end_at:
855            datetime end range for filtering transactions in full date-time.
856        """
857        # if a specific page is provided, we just get that page;
858        # otherwise, we loop through all pages
859        paginate = False
860        if page_offset is None:
861            page_offset = 0
862            paginate = True
863        params = {
864            "per-page": per_page,
865            "page-offset": page_offset,
866            "sort": sort,
867            "type": type,
868            "types[]": types,
869            "sub-type[]": sub_types,
870            "start-date": start_date,
871            "end-date": end_date,
872            "instrument-type": instrument_type.value if instrument_type else None,
873            "symbol": symbol,
874            "underlying-symbol": underlying_symbol,
875            "action": action,
876            "partition-key": partition_key,
877            "futures-symbol": futures_symbol,
878            "start-at": start_at,
879            "end-at": end_at,
880        }
881        # loop through pages and get all transactions
882        txns = []
883        while True:
884            response = await session.async_client.get(
885                f"/accounts/{self.account_number}/transactions",
886                params={
887                    k: v  # type: ignore
888                    for k, v in params.items()
889                    if v is not None
890                },
891            )
892            validate_response(response)
893            json = response.json()
894            txns.extend([Transaction(**i) for i in json["data"]["items"]])
895            # handle pagination
896            pagination = json["pagination"]
897            if (
898                pagination["page-offset"] >= pagination["total-pages"] - 1
899                or not paginate
900            ):
901                break
902            params["page-offset"] += 1  # type: ignore
903
904        return txns

981                params={
982                    k: v  # type: ignore
983                    for k, v in params.items()
984                    if v is not None
985                },

199    public watchlist updates, quote alerts, and user-level messages. It should
200    always be initialized as an async context manager, or by awaiting it,
201    since the object cannot be fully instantiated without async.

203    Example usage::
204
205        from tastytrade import Account, AlertStreamer
206        from tastytrade.order import PlacedOrder
207

209            accounts = Account.get_accounts(session)

213            # changes in public watchlists
214            await streamer.subscribe_public_watchlists()
215            # quote alerts configured by the user

291        """
292        Connect to the websocket server using the URL and authorization
293        token provided during initialization.
294        """
295        reconnecting = False
296        self._disconnect_called = False

298            self._websocket = websocket
299            self._heartbeat_task = asyncio.create_task(self._heartbeat())
300            logger.debug("Websocket connection established.")

303                self._reconnect_task = asyncio.create_task(
304                    self.reconnect_fn(self, *self.reconnect_args)
305                )
306            try:
307                async for raw_message in websocket:
308                    logger.debug("raw message: %s", raw_message)
309                    data = json.loads(raw_message)
310                    type_str = data.get("type")
311                    if type_str is not None:
312                        await self._map_message(type_str, data["data"])
313            except ConnectionClosed as e:

315            except asyncio.CancelledError:
316                logger.debug("Websocket interrupted, cancelling main loop.")
317                asyncio.create_task(self.close())
318                return
319            finally:
320                asyncio.create_task(self.disconnect_fn(self, *self.disconnect_args))
321            logger.debug("Websocket connection closed, retrying...")
322            reconnecting = True

Used to subscribe to account-level updates (balances, orders, positions), public watchlist updates, quote alerts, and user-level messages. It should always be initialized as an async context manager, or by awaiting it, since the object cannot be fully instantiated without async.

513    async def _connect(self) -> None:
514        """
515        Connect to the websocket server using the URL and
516        authorization token provided during initialization.
517        """
518        reconnecting = False
519        self._disconnect_called = False
520        async for websocket in connect(
521            self._wss_url, ssl=self._ssl_context, proxy=self.proxy
522        ):
523            self._websocket = websocket
524            await self._setup_connection()
525            try:
526                async for raw_message in websocket:
527                    message = json.loads(raw_message)
528                    logger.debug("received: %s", message)
529                    if (
530                        message["type"] == "FEED_DATA"
531                    ):  # This is the most common message type
532                        await self._map_message(message["data"])
533                    elif message["type"] == "SETUP":
534                        await self._authenticate_connection()
535                    elif message["type"] == "AUTH_STATE":
536                        if message["state"] == "AUTHORIZED":
537                            logger.debug("Websocket connection established.")
538                            self._authenticated = True
539                            self._heartbeat_task = asyncio.create_task(
540                                self._heartbeat()
541                            )
542                        # run reconnect hook upon auth completion
543                        if reconnecting:
544                            self._subscription_state.clear()
545                            reconnecting = False
546                            self._reconnect_task = asyncio.create_task(
547                                self.reconnect_fn(self, *self.reconnect_args)
548                            )
549                    elif message["type"] == "CHANNEL_OPENED":
550                        channel = next(
551                            k
552                            for k, v in self._channels.items()
553                            if v == message["channel"]
554                        )
555                        self._subscription_state[channel] = "CHANNEL_OPENED"
556                        logger.debug("Channel opened: %s", message)
557                    elif message["type"] == "CHANNEL_CLOSED":
558                        channel = next(
559                            k
560                            for k, v in self._channels.items()
561                            if v == message["channel"]
562                        )
563                        del self._subscription_state[channel]
564                        logger.debug("Channel closed: %s", message)
565                    elif message["type"] == "FEED_CONFIG":
566                        logger.debug("Feed configured: %s", message)
567                    elif message["type"] == "KEEPALIVE":
568                        pass
569                    elif message["type"] == "ERROR":
570                        logger.error(f"Fatal streamer error: {message['message']}")
571                        asyncio.create_task(self.close())
572                        return
573                    else:
574                        logger.error(f"Unknown message: {message}")
575            except ConnectionClosed as e:
576                logger.error(f"Websocket connection closed with {e}")
577                if e.rcvd and e.rcvd.code == 1009:
578                    logger.error(
579                        "Subscription message too long! Try reducing the number of symbols."
580                    )
581                    asyncio.create_task(self.close())
582                    return
583            except asyncio.CancelledError:
584                logger.debug("Websocket interrupted, cancelling main loop.")
585                asyncio.create_task(self.close())
586                return
587            finally:
588                asyncio.create_task(self.disconnect_fn(self, *self.disconnect_args))
589            logger.debug("Websocket connection closed, retrying...")
590            reconnecting = True

671    async def subscribe(
672        self,
673        event_class: Type[EventType],
674        symbols: list[str],
675        refresh_interval: float = 0.1,
676    ) -> None:
677        """
678        Subscribes to quotes for given list of symbols. Used for recurring data
679        feeds.
680        For candles, use :meth:`subscribe_candle` instead.
681
682        :param event_class: type of subscription to add, should be of :any:`EventType`
683        :param symbols: list of symbols to subscribe for
684        :param refresh_interval: Time in seconds between fetching new events from dxfeed for this event_class.
685            You can try a higher value if processing quote updates quickly is not a high priority.
686            Once refresh_interval is set for this event_class and channel is opened, it cannot be changed later.
687        """
688        cls_str = MAP_EVENTS_REVERSE[event_class]
689        if self._subscription_state[cls_str] != "CHANNEL_OPENED":
690            await self._channel_request(cls_str, refresh_interval)
691        message = {
692            "type": "FEED_SUBSCRIPTION",
693            "channel": self._channels[cls_str],
694            "add": [{"symbol": symbol, "type": cls_str} for symbol in symbols],
695        }
696        logger.debug("sending subscription: %s", message)
697        await self._websocket.send(json.dumps(message))

723        logger.debug("sending subscription: %s", message)
724        await self._websocket.send(json.dumps(message))
725        time_out = 100
726        while not self._subscription_state[event_type] == "CHANNEL_OPENED":
727            await asyncio.sleep(0.1)
728            time_out -= 1
729            if time_out <= 0:
730                raise TastytradeError("Subscription channel not opened")
731        # setup the feed
732        await self._channel_setup(event_type, refresh_interval)
733
734    async def _channel_setup(
735        self, event_type: str, refresh_interval: float = 0.1
736    ) -> None:
737        message = {
738            "type": "FEED_SETUP",
739            "channel": self._channels[event_type],
740            "acceptAggregationPeriod": refresh_interval,
741            "acceptDataFormat": "COMPACT",
742        }
743
744        def dict_from_schema(event_class: Any):
745            schema = event_class.schema()
746            return {schema["title"]: list(schema["properties"].keys())}
747
748        cls = MAP_EVENTS[event_type]
749        accept = dict_from_schema(cls)
750        message["acceptEventFields"] = accept
751        # send message
752        logger.debug("setting up feed: %s", message)
753        await self._websocket.send(json.dumps(message))
754

849    async def _map_message(self, message) -> None:
850        """
851        Takes the raw JSON data, parses the events and places them into their
852        respective queues.
853
854        :param message: raw JSON data from the websocket
855        """
856        logger.debug("received message: %s", message)
857        if isinstance(message[0], str):
858            msg_type = message[0]
859        else:
860            msg_type = message[0][0]
861        data = message[1]
862        # parse type or warn for unknown type
863        if msg_type not in MAP_EVENTS:
864            logger.fatal(
865                f"Unknown message type {msg_type} received: {data}, please open an issue!"
866            )
867        else:
868            cls: Event = MAP_EVENTS[msg_type]
869            results = cls.from_stream(data)
870            for r in results:
871                await self._queues[msg_type].put(r)

A DXLinkStreamer object is used to fetch quotes or greeks for a given symbol or list of symbols. It should always be initialized as an async context manager, or by awaiting it, since the object cannot be fully instantiated without async.

Example usage::

from tastytrade import DXLinkStreamer
from tastytrade.dxfeed import Quote

# must be a production session
async with DXLinkStreamer(session) as streamer:
    subs = ['SPY']  # list of quotes to subscribe to
    await streamer.subscribe(Quote, subs)
    quote = await streamer.get_event(Quote)
    print(quote)

500    async def close(self) -> None:
501        """
502        Closes the websocket connection and cancels the heartbeat task.
503        """
504        self._connect_task.cancel()
505        self._heartbeat_task.cancel()
506        tasks = [self._connect_task, self._heartbeat_task]
507        if self._reconnect_task is not None and not self._reconnect_task.done():
508            self._reconnect_task.cancel()
509            tasks.append(self._reconnect_task)
510        await asyncio.gather(*tasks)
511        await self._websocket.wait_closed()

Contains a local user login which can then be used to interact with the remote API.

Parameters
  • login: Tastytrade username or email
  • remember_me: whether or not to create a remember token to use instead of a password
  • password: tastytrade password to login; if absent, remember token is required
  • remember_token: previously generated token; if absent, password is required
  • is_test: whether to use the test API endpoints, default False
  • two_factor_authentication: if two factor authentication is enabled, this is the code sent to the user's device
  • dxfeed_tos_compliant: whether to use the dxfeed TOS-compliant API endpoint for the streamer
  • proxy: if provided, all requests will be made through this proxy, as well as web socket connections for streamers.
Session( login: str, password: Optional[str] = None, remember_me: bool = False, remember_token: Optional[str] = None, is_test: bool = False, two_factor_authentication: Optional[str] = None, dxfeed_tos_compliant: bool = False, proxy: Optional[str] = None) 
293    def __init__(
294        self,
295        login: str,
296        password: Optional[str] = None,
297        remember_me: bool = False,
298        remember_token: Optional[str] = None,
299        is_test: bool = False,
300        two_factor_authentication: Optional[str] = None,
301        dxfeed_tos_compliant: bool = False,
302        proxy: Optional[str] = None,
303    ):
304        body = {"login": login, "remember-me": remember_me}
305        if password is not None:
306            body["password"] = password
307        elif remember_token is not None:
308            body["remember-token"] = remember_token
309        else:
310            raise TastytradeError(
311                "You must provide a password or remember token to log in."
312            )
313        #: Whether this is a cert or real session
314        self.is_test = is_test
315        #: Proxy URL to use for requests and web sockets
316        self.proxy = proxy
317        # The headers to use for API requests
318        headers = {
319            "Accept": "application/json",
320            "Content-Type": "application/json",
321        }
322        #: httpx client for sync requests
323        self.sync_client = Client(
324            base_url=(CERT_URL if is_test else API_URL), headers=headers, proxy=proxy
325        )
326        if two_factor_authentication is not None:
327            response = self.sync_client.post(
328                "/sessions",
329                json=body,
330                headers={"X-Tastyworks-OTP": two_factor_authentication},
331            )
332        else:
333            response = self.sync_client.post("/sessions", json=body)
334        data = validate_and_parse(response)
335        #: The user dict returned by the API; contains basic user information
336        self.user = User(**data["user"])
337        #: The session token used to authenticate requests
338        self.session_token = data["session-token"]
339        #: A single-use token which can be used to login without a password
340        self.remember_token = data.get("remember-token")
341        self.sync_client.headers.update({"Authorization": self.session_token})
342        #: httpx client for async requests
343        self.async_client = AsyncClient(
344            base_url=self.sync_client.base_url,
345            headers=self.sync_client.headers.copy(),
346            proxy=proxy,
347        )
348        #: expiration for session token
349        self.session_expiration = datetime.fromisoformat(
350            data["session-expiration"].replace("Z", "+00:00")
351        )
352
353        # Pull streamer tokens and urls
354        url = (
355            "/api-quote-tokens"
356            if dxfeed_tos_compliant or is_test
357            else "/quote-streamer-tokens"
358        )
359        data = self._get(url)
360
361        #: Auth token for dxfeed websocket
362        self.streamer_token = data["token"]
363        #: URL for dxfeed websocket
364        self.dxlink_url = data["dxlink-url"]
365        #: expiration for streamer token
366        exp = data.get("expires-at")
367        self.streamer_expiration = (
368            datetime.fromisoformat(exp.replace("Z", "+00:00")) if exp else None
369        )
